benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/block - Block a bundle

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25, @TC26, @TC27, @TC29 cover successful creation with valid data.
Invalid Payload: @TC08 covers malformed request body, missing required fields, invalid types.
Missing Required Header: @TC09 covers missing X-Killbill-CreatedBy header.
Missing Request Body: @TC10 covers absence of request body.
Invalid bundleId format: @TC06 covers invalid format, @TC07 covers non-existent bundleId.
Non-existent bundleId: @TC07 covers not found scenario.
Maximum/Minimum values: @TC13 and @TC14 cover boundary testing with max/min data.
Partial input: @TC15 covers partial data submission.
Injection and XSS: @TC19 and @TC20 cover injection and XSS payloads.
Concurrency and retries: @TC22 and @TC21 cover concurrent requests and network retries.
Special characters: @TC23 covers special characters in input.
Backward compatibility: @TC24 covers previous client expectations.
Performance: @TC25, @TC26, @TC27 cover response times and resource utilization.
Dependency errors: @TC28 covers dependent service failures.
Data consistency: @TC29 covers system-wide data reflection.
gaps: Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized or invalid tokens.
Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or rate limiting scenarios.
Caching Behavior: No tests for cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Pagination: No tests for handling large datasets with pagination.
Service Unavailability: No explicit tests for server downtime or 503 errors beyond @TC17.
Accessibility: Only @TC30 mentions documentation accessibility, no direct API accessibility tests.
recommendations: Add tests for authorization failures, invalid tokens, and permission checks.
Include rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system robustness under load.
Implement tests for caching headers to ensure proper cache control.
Create scenarios for pagination handling with large datasets.
Add explicit tests for server downtime, 503 errors, and recovery procedures.
Develop accessibility tests for API documentation and error messages for compliance.
